## Design System — Rightmove + Louvre Abu Dhabi

Inspired by **Rightmove** (functionality, layout, clarity) and **Louvre Abu Dhabi** (calm, typography, space). Clean, professional, editorial.

### Colours
- Background: `cream` (#F8F4EE)
- Primary accent (links, CTAs): `primary` (#1e3a5f navy-slate), hover `primary-hover` (#2d4a6f). Use for buttons, links, and key actions.
- Text: `charcoal` (#1A1A1A), muted `charcoal-muted` (#7A756E), light `charcoal-light` (#4A4540)
- Card background: `warm-white` (#FDFBF8)
- Borders: `warm-border` (#E8E2D9), `warm-border-light` (#F0EBE3)
- Legacy `hermes` remains in Tailwind for reference but use `primary` in new and updated UI.

### Typography
- Headlines: `font-display` → Cormorant Garamond (serif)
- Body: `font-body` → Inter (sans-serif)
- Use the custom class names (`font-display`, `font-body`), not raw `font-serif`/`font-sans`.
- **Scale:** Prefer theme tokens over arbitrary sizes: `text-body-sm` (0.9375rem), `text-body-xs` (0.8125rem), `text-label-xs` (0.6875rem), `text-label-sm` (0.75rem), `text-display-sm` / `text-display-md` / `text-display-lg` / `text-display-xl` for display type; Tailwind `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg` where appropriate.

### Layout Rules
- Generous whitespace; hairline borders (1px), warm-toned
- No heavy drop shadows (or very subtle)
- Buttons: outline (charcoal) or solid primary; not rounded/bubbly
- High information density where needed, but calm and scannable (Rightmove-style cards and filters)

### Hover Behaviour
- Use `card-title-hover` class on Link elements for card titles
- globals.css uses `@media (hover: hover)` so hovers don’t stick on touch
- Prefer `hover:text-primary-hover` (or equivalent) over inline group-hover where possible

